@node OVERVIEW "Overview"

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****

         *******************************

               MicroDot 2 Voyager

                   Overview

         *******************************

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****



  MD2V (MicroDot to Voyager) is simply an ARexx script designed
to allow the user to either use the pull-down menu or to create
their own button to open an HTML based eMail in a Voyager Window.
The ARexx script uses the .mdrx naming convention so that MicroDot
will automatically place the script into it's ARexx Menu.

  Basically,@{b} I @{ub}got tired of HTML based eMails! Thus,
the idea was born.  I initially wrote the script just for myself,
but then decided to write an installer and to give it away.


  The ARexx script relies heavily upon what the Installer does,
as it isn't a direct copy.  The Installer builds the ARexx script
based upon input from the user.  You might even say that Installer
is the actual author of the ARexx script...


Since AWeb, IBrowse, and Voyager seem to use different pathing
methods to local files, OpenURL didn't quite to work.  So, the
Installer had to manipulate the ARexx file to hardcode into the
ARexx script the location of Voyager on your system--this was
done in case the ARexx port VOYAGER isn't open at the time the
script is activated.

  The only extra libraries needed for this script is the incredily
delicious ReqTools.library and RexxReqTools.library, and both
are available on the @{" Aminet " SYSTEM "OpenURL us.aminet.net"}.


@{fg fill}* @{b}NEW@{ub} *@{fg text}  In version 1.1

    A maintenance upgrade, fixes a bug that causes a possible
    crash under certain circumstances.

@{fg fill}* @{b}NEW@{ub} *@{fg text}  In version 1.0

    If you choose not to have a requester when starting Voyager,
    you will not be asked if you want to start Voyager, and the
    ARexx script will wait on the Voyager ARexx port to open.
    In other words, all actions will be automatic!  Also, the
    mail will not open a new window.  If the requestor option
    is selected, actions will be the same as the previous
    release.

  I hope that people use and enjoy the ARexx Script!

-- The Author
   David Crawford

@endnode
@node REQ "Requirements"

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****

         *******************************

             MicroDot 2 Voyager MDRX

               System Requirements

         *******************************

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****



The following is needed to use this script.  The button
links utilize OpenURL to launch a browser window to the
site or download file mentioned.

1. An Amiga with a TCP/IP stack.

2. The following @{" Vapor " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.vapor.com"} products:
   A. @{" MicroDot-2 " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.vapor.com/md2/"}
   B. @{" Voyager    " SYSTEM "OpenURL v3.vapor.com"}

3. ARexx must be active (naturally).

4. These Libraries (available on the @{" AmiNet " SYSTEM "OpenURL us.aminet.net"} ).
   A.  ReqTools       @{" http://www.aminet.net/~aminet/util/libs/ReqToolsUsr.lha " SYSTEM "OpenURL http://www.aminet.net/~aminet/util/libs/ReqToolsUsr.lha  "}
   B.  RexxReqTools   @{" http://www.aminet.net/~aminet/util/rexx/RexxReqTools.lha " SYSTEM "OpenURL http://www.aminet.net/~aminet/util/rexx/RexxReqTools.lha"}
   C.  Installer version 42 or above







NOTE: Use the supplied installer, as it builds the ARexx script
      dynamically.


@endnode
