@node INSTALL "Install"

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****

         *******************************

             MicroDot 2 Voyager MDRX

                  Installation

         *******************************

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****


The Installer:

The installer is not only a convenience, but a requirement.
It dynamically builds a custom ARexx script based on the user's
specifications and system configuration.

Upon launching the installer, you will be asked to provide several
answers to questions regarding your preferences and system.

In a nutshell, you will be asked to provide:

1. The location of the MicroDot2 directory on your system.
   (used to @{i}install@{ui} the script to the correct location)

2. The location of the Voyager executable on your system.
   (used to create the ARexx script's ability to open Voyager.)

3. Whether or not you want to be bothered with a requester to
   start Voyager.
   (The script can just try to launch Voyager if it isn't already
    running, or it will ask for permission first.)

3. Whether or not you want a requester asking to delete the
   temporary file.
   (The script will extract the message to a tempfile, so you
    can have it delete the file immediately after loading it
    into Voyager. Or, you may opt to have it ask you for
    permission each time.)

4. Whether or not you want the documentation copied.

5. Finally, you will be asked if you want the button copied,
   and where you may want it copied to.

At this point, the installer will build your custom Arexx script.
For usage and configuration, please see the @{"usage" link USAGE} section.



@endnode
