@node USAGE "Usage"

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****

         *******************************

             MicroDot 2 Voyager MDRX

                      @{b}USAGE@{ub}

         *******************************

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****


Warning, do not use this script as a filter!

To utilize MD2V.mdrx, simply select a message, and select
MD2V.mdrx from MicroDot2's ARexx pull down menu.

The message can be selected from the @{b}group-list@{ub} window as
a highlighted message, or from the @{b}message-reader@{ub} window.
In the case of multiple selections in the group-list window, the
last item selected will be sent to Voyager.

Note: regular text emails can also be sent to Voyager, although
      the formatting will be lost.

If Voyager is not currently running, MD2V will launch Voyager for
you.

@{fg fill}If you opted to be asked first@{fg text}, the requester will appear.
Once Voyager is running, another requester will appear asking you
to press "OK" when Voyager has finished loading.  When Voyager has
finished loading, press the button. The message will be displayed
in a new window.

@{fg fill}If you opted @{fg shine}NOT@{fg text} to be asked first@{fg text}, Voyager will start automatically.
When the Voyager port is open, the message will be displayed in the
in the main Voyager window.

At this point, the temporary file will be deleted, or the requester
will ask you for permission to do so (depending on your choice at
install time).


@{b}@{u}EXTRA HINTS: @{uu}@{ub}

From the General Settings menu in MicroDot2, an extra button can be
created to start MD2V.  The Group List and Message Reader each have
their own button banks, and will have to be configured separately.

How To:

Click @{" HERE " SYSTEM "run >NIL: Sys:Utilities/Multiview prefs.iff"} for a window grab of a configured copy of Microdot-2.

Open Microdot-2's General Preferences menu selection, or if MicroDot
is currently running, click @{" HERE " SYSTEM "rx 'address MD.1 OpenPrefswin'"}.

Select Buttons from the list on the left.

Select the tab for either @{u}Message list buttons@{uu} or @{u}Msg reader buttons@{uu}.

Select an unused button from the button bank on the top of the page.

Use the requester button to select an image (if one is desired).

Type "_HTML" or "_MD2V" into the Label text box.

Enter a hotkey if one is desired.

In the Action string gadget, enter the full path to MD2V.mdrx.
(example: Netconnect3:Programs/Microdot2/Rexx/MD2V.mdrx)

Select "OK" from the bottom of the window to save.

Afterwards, you will be able to use the selected button to activate
MD2V instead of using the menu.


@endnode
