@node NOTES "Notes"


         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****

         *******************************

             MicroDot 2 Voyager MDRX

               @{b}IMPORTANT NOTE@{ub}

         *******************************

         *****@{" A m i g a  Z o n e " SYSTEM "OpenURL www.amigazone.com"}*****


    As of this writing, there is a bug in Microdot-2 that may or
  may not affect the user of MD2V.

    MD2V is an ARexx script that uses the Microdot naming convention
  of #?.mdrx, so MicroDot-II will scan it at startup placing it in
  the ARexx menu.  However, it seems as if ANY mdrx script scanned
  into the third position of this menu (or greater) will suffer from
  unexpected results.  Therefore, if you already have @{b}TWO@{ub} (2) mdrx scripts
  in your menu, you may want to change the suffix of MD2V to "@{fg shine}.rexx@{fg text}",
  and follow the instructions given to use MD2V from a button.

  See @{" Usage " link USAGE} to learn how to set MD2V to launch from a button.


@endnode


